# The desktop allowlist bridge artifact is compared BYTE-FOR-BYTE against a
# fresh render by tests/desktop-allowlist-drift.test.ts and embedded verbatim
# into the Rust crate via include_str!. Pin it to LF so core.autocrlf=true
# checkouts (Windows dev machines) don't rewrite it to CRLF and fail the
# drift test / change the embedded bytes.
desktop-agent/src-tauri/generated/*.json text eol=lf

# The agent-ingest contract fixture (T4.1) is likewise compared byte-for-byte
# by tests/desktop-ingest-fixture-drift.test.ts and embedded verbatim into the
# Rust crate via include_str! in sync/batch.rs — pin it to LF for the same
# reason as the allowlist artifact above.
desktop-agent/src-tauri/fixtures/*.json text eol=lf
